---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Refund Policy - Waterm"
  description="Refund Policy for Waterm Pro purchases through Apple's App Store."
  canonicalPath="/refund"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Refund Policy" lastUpdated="January 15, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>Refunds for App Store Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Waterm Pro is sold through Apple’s App Store. Apple handles billing and refunds, and eligibility
        is determined by Apple’s policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How to Request a Refund</h2>
      <p>To request a refund, use Apple’s official process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com">reportaproblem.apple.com</a></li>
        <li>Sign in with your Apple ID</li>
        <li>Find your Waterm Pro purchase</li>
        <li>Select "Request a refund" and follow the prompts</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        We’re unable to issue refunds directly, but if you’re having trouble using the app, contact us
        and we’ll do our best to help.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Subscription Cancellation</h2>
      <p>If you subscribed to Waterm Pro Monthly or Yearly, you can cancel at any time:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open Settings on your iPhone or iPad, or System Settings on Mac</li>
        <li>Tap your Apple ID, then Subscriptions</li>
        <li>Find Waterm and tap "Cancel Subscription"</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Upon cancellation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You'll retain Pro access until the end of your current billing period</li>
        <li>No further charges will be made</li>
        <li>Pro features will be disabled after the period ends</li>
        <li>Your servers and workspaces will remain, but free tier limits will apply</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Lifetime Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Lifetime Pro purchases are one-time and do not require cancellation. Refunds are handled by
        Apple using the same process above.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or technical issues? Contact <a href="mailto:waterm@vivy.company">waterm@vivy.company</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
